', 'Draw quadrilateral $ABCD$ with vertices $A(-2, 2)$, $B(5,-1)$, $C(6,2)$, and $D(-1,5)$ on the grid below. Prove that $ABCD$ is a parallelogram by using slopes to show $\overline{AB} || \overline{CD}$ and $\overline{AD} || \overline{BC}$. \\[0.25cm]
  Calculate the slopes.
  \begin{flushright}
    \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=.635]
